"""
ensemble.py
===========
Gradient-boosted tree ensemble — Stage 2 of the hybrid fraud detection
framework.

Paper
-----
"A Hybrid Deep Learning and Explainable AI Framework for Real-Time
Financial Fraud Detection in Dynamic Environments"

Role in the hybrid pipeline
----------------------------
This module implements f_w : R^k -> [0,1], the decision layer that
receives the DNN latent embedding z = phi_theta(x) from Stage 1
(model.py) and produces a calibrated fraud probability score:

    s = f_w(z)  =  P_hat(y = 1 | z)

followed by a cost-optimal threshold decision:

    delta*(x) = 1  iff  P_hat(y = 1 | z) >= tau*
    tau* = c_FP / (c_FP + c_FN)

Paper references (System Model & Methodology sections)
------------------------------------------------------
"The decision layer uses a gradient-boosted tree ensemble trained on
the fused representation z to produce a score."

"The depth of the tree, number of estimators and the learning rate
were optimized (Bayesian optimization) to trade off predictive accuracy
and inference speed."

"An isotonic regressor with the latest validation window is used to
score-calibrate the scores so they match the observed frequencies, and
then a cost-sensitive threshold tau* is used."

"Cost-sensitive analysis, at real cost ratios, where the cost of a
missed fraud is as many as 100 times the cost of a false alert, shows
that the hybrid model saves financial loss per 100,000 transactions."

Design decisions
----------------
1.  Both XGBoost and LightGBM are supported.  The paper benchmarks
    both; the EnsembleHead class wraps either backend uniformly.
2.  Bayesian hyperparameter search via Optuna optimises PR-AUC
    (not ROC-AUC) because PR-AUC is more informative under extreme
    class imbalance (paper: "particular attention is paid to recall").
3.  Isotonic regression calibration reduces ECE from ~6% to <2%
    as reported in Table 2.
4.  Cost-sensitive threshold tau* = c_FP / (c_FP + c_FN) is derived
    from Lemma 1 in the paper and applied after calibration.
5.  scale_pos_weight (XGBoost) / scale_pos_weight (LightGBM) handle
    the raw class imbalance in the embedding space.

Usage
-----
    from src.ensemble import EnsembleHead, train_ensemble_fold, train_all_folds

    # Train on DNN embeddings from a single fold
    head, history = train_ensemble_fold(
        Z_train, y_train, Z_val, y_val,
        backend="xgboost",
        n_trials=30,
    )

    # Score new embeddings
    probs     = head.predict_proba(Z_test)      # calibrated probabilities
    decisions = head.predict(Z_test)            # 0 / 1 using tau*
    cost      = head.cost_per_100k(y_test, Z_test)

    # Save / load
    head.save("results/models/ensemble_fold0.pkl")
    head = EnsembleHead.load("results/models/ensemble_fold0.pkl")
"""

